From 2b30d482f0c8656895dc935cf006960d16a790a1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jake Teton-Landis <just.1.jake@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 12:03:55 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Add external-runtime introspection channel for external state
 libraries

Exposes, via ReactSharedInternals (the onStartTransitionFinish pattern):
- unstable_subscribeToExternalRuntime: render-pass start/end, commit
  (with committed/remaining lanes), and before/after host-mutation events,
  all keyed by the root's container. The mutation bracket lives in
  flushMutationEffects so View Transition commits are bracketed correctly.
- unstable_getCurrentUpdateLane / unstable_getRenderContext /
  unstable_isTransitionLane / unstable_lanesInclude: lane attribution for
  external writes and world selection for external reads during render.

Lanes cross the boundary as opaque numbers; no Fiber/FiberRoot shapes leak.
All hooks are inert (one property read + branch) until a listener subscribes.
